summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsCruelty FreeMeet your perfect matte with Morphe's Soulmatte Velvet Lip Mousse. An infusion of indulgent color and a comfortable air-whipped texture that melts into lips, this innovative formulation resists settling into lip lines, smudging, or fading for a seamless, soft-focus effect, and velvety smooth feel.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I really like this shade - a version of it was my absolute favorite for many years & it's giving me the 2016 vibes I crave! I miss the "dusty rose" trend & so glad to see an updated version of it here in the shade "Dearest". It's a little more on the nude/warm toned side, but I feel it darkens/cools down a bit once it dries. It's a great every day color for bold looks or toned down looks in my opinion.

  As for the formula, it's smooth, creamy, & full coverage. It also dried down about 95%, though I will say that anywhere I had dry/peeling skin on my lips, it stayed a bit tacky. So you'll want to hydrate & exfoliate ahead of time with this one for best results. I also found it to be a little heavy, but for a full coverage formula it wasn't uncomfortable like many others out there. I'd compare it to a slightly more comfortable & less transferable NYX Lip Lingerie for those who are a fan of that formula - this one for you! I vape so I was able to notice the little bit of transfer, but there wasn't much so I'd say it's 90% "kiss proof" for those looking for that type of formula. As a makeup artist, I can happily say I'd likely reach for this as an affordable option on a wedding day look since it stayed put & was comfortable enough for hours of wear!

 After a while (approx. 3 hours) I did feel like my lips got dry (as with any liquid lippie) so I tested it with both a lip balm & gloss over top. I found the lip balm to mesh a little better with the formula & both of them revived my lips & the color for several more hours of wear. 

 All in all I would get this color & product again, which was sent to me in exchange for a review. I recommend trying it out!
faceoff_positive.headline: Beautiful Full Coverage Everyday Shade

faceoff_negative.comments:
I was able to try Morphe Velvet Mouse Soulmate through Bizz Agent! I am so thankful for the opportunity because I am in love with this lip product! 

The velvet mousse along with hydrafill lip liner has been a game changer! I have a scar at the corner of my lip, so sometimes certain lip products enhance attention to the scar. However, with Morphe Velvet Mousse I was able to basically disguise my scar! 

The Velvet Mousse seems a little thick when just looking at on the applicator. However, just little bit goes a long way! The matte color is absolutely stunning! It does not flake and appears smooth and natural on lips. 

However, if you do put too much you can expect some on your teeth or for it to smear. So just use a little bit or wipe off excess. 

The color soulmate was a perfect match for my skin tone! I have brown eyes, a warm undertone skin color, and brown hair with face framing highlights. I use alot of natural eyeshadow, a peachy pink blush, and the soulmate color was the perfect addition to make up color scheme. I used the Morphe Hydrafill Gel lip liner with the Morphe Velvet Mousse when I had more of glam smokey eye look, and a natural soft eyeshadow. The Soulmate  lip color with matte finish looked perfect with any style of make up I did. 

I will definitely be using Morphe Velvet Mousee and hydraffill lipliner as the finishing touch to my makeup routines. 

Again, I am so thankfull to Bizz Agent for this opportunity. 

The package the Morphe Lipliner and Velevet Mousse came in added to the excitement, it was soo beautiful and thrilling to open! I can't wait to order more colors. 

The only thing I wish is that the color lasted all day. I notcied at about 2 or 3 hours after initial application I either needed to touch up, or reapply.
faceoff_negative.headline: Morphe Velvet Mousse is officially my favorite lip product!
